To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Pennsylvania Right to Know Act, I hereby request the following records:

Subject: STATE CONSTABLE GLENN MARKLEY Records Request

1. About Samuel Glenn Markley (aka GLENN MARKLEY) or any PERSON he uses (e.g. INCARCERATE INC) provide the following:
A. CONSTABLE'S OATH OF OFFICE;
B. Constable's Bond;
C. CONSTABLE ORDER;
D. CONSTABLE AFFIDAVIT;
E. CONSTABLE PETITION;
F. Constable number;
G. Authorization Agreement for Automatic Deposits;
H. Vendor payment/transaction history for 2024, 2025 and 2026 to date;

2. About Samuel Glenn Markley (aka GLENN MARKLEY) or any PERSON he uses (e.g. INCARCERATE INC) additionally, provide the following:
A. proof of election or appointment or court order;
B. proof of PCCD training and certification;
C. proof of firearm certification if applicable;
D. verification that all forms required by the office of the Chester County Controller have been filed including W-9 and proof of insurance;
E. contract between the Constable and Chester County approved by the Board of Commissioners;
F. completed Constable/Deputy Constable Information Sheet;
G. copies of all required clearances;
H. proof of valid driver's license;
I. proof of motor vehicle insurance;

3. About DISTRICT COURT #15-4-03 all correspondence records including list of dated multimedia attachments (photos, video clips, etc.) with Samuel Glenn Markley (aka GLENN MARKLEY) or any PERSON he uses (e.g. INCARCERATE INC) related to any service provided to locations in West Whiteland Township (Chester County Pennsylvania) between August 1st 2025 and March 31st 2026;

4. About DISTRICT COURT #15-4-03 all vendor fees and payments/transactions to Samuel Glenn Markley (aka GLENN MARKLEY) or any PERSON he uses (e.g. INCARCERATE INC) related to any service (listing case numbers for each) provided to locations in West Whiteland Township (Chester County Pennsylvania) between April 1st 2024 and March 31st 2026.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

David Murray High
